ie.gmit.sw.base

Class SingleThreadMapBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • ie.gmit.sw.base.MapBuilder
      • ie.gmit.sw.base.SingleThreadMapBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.concurrent.Callable<CounterMap<java.lang.Integer>>

    public class SingleThreadMapBuilder
extends MapBuilder
    Build map of shingles from a file using a single thread, good enough for the design because CounterMaps can counts one shingle at a time.

    Use a input of Number that are the hash code of the shingles(they are basically used as shingles), count appearance of each number in the queue using a CounterMap<Integer>.

    Author:
    Jose I. Retamal
